PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530806\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530806\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104oys1665702649554.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oys1665702649554.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oys1665702649554.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"oys1665702649554\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">DLLs that provide COM support on Intel-based platforms\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oys1665702649554__section_w5622ab1b5b1_w5623ab1b5_w5624ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"oys1665702649554__table_d18611e1_d18612e1_d18613e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default location:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceAPSInstallDir</var>/common/bin</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oys1665702649554__section_w5625ab1b5b3_w5626ab1b5_w5627ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d838929e80\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oys1665702649554__p_d176522e1_d176523e1_d176524e1\"><span class=\"ph filepath\">uComDrv.dll</span> is the COM\n            connector DLL that implements the Uniface-COM interface. It is required if the Uniface\n            application is performing COM call-out or call-in, and must reside in the Uniface\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">bin</span> directory.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oys1665702649554__p_d176525e1_d176526e1_d176527e1\"><span class=\"ph filepath\">uComSkl.dll</span> is a skeleton DLL\n            file used during the creation of Uniface COM Interface DLL files. It is required if you\n            want to generate COM Interface DLL files for Uniface services.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oys1665702649554__section_w5628ab1b5b5_w5629ab1b5_w5630ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d838929e99\">Runtime Environment </h2>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"oys1665702649554__note_w5631ab1b5b5b3_w5632ab1b5b5_w5633ab1b5_w5634ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The developer\n            is responsible for including the <span class=\"ph filepath\">uComDrv.dll</span>.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oys1665702649554__p_d176531e1_d176532e1_d176533e1\">For COM clients to create instances of Uniface services (call-in), you must have the exported COM Interface DLL for the services on the workstation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oys1665702649554__p_d176534e1_d176535e1_d176536e1\">You need to register the exported COM Interface DLL in the workstation’s Microsoft Windows Registry. This is handled by the self-registering capability of the DLL, and the standard Microsoft Windows <code class=\"ph codeph\">REGSVR32</code> command. For example, to register the definitions contained in the file <span class=\"ph filepath\">SERVS.DLL</span>, use the following command:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oys1665702649554__p_d176537e1_d176538e1_d176539e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">REGSVR32 SERVS.DLL</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oys1665702649554__p_d176540e1_d176541e1_d176542e1\">For COM call-out, the assignment file must contain the appropriate reference to the COM connector path for the desired components.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"oys1665702649554__note_w5635ab1b5b5c13_w5636ab1b5b5_w5637ab1b5_w5638ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> COM-specific assignment file settings are not required if COM is specified as the default implementation in the Signature Editor.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530806\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530806\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uComDrv.dll and uComSkl.dll Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 DLLs that provide COM support on Intel-based platforms Default location: UnifaceAPSInstallDir /common/bin Description uComDrv.dll is the COM connector DLL that implements the Uniface-COM interface. It is required if the Uniface application is performing COM call-out or call-in, and must reside in the Uniface bin directory. uComSkl.dll is a skeleton DLL file used during the creation of Uniface COM Interface DLL files. It is required if you want to generate COM Interface DLL files for Uniface services. Runtime Environment Note: The developer is responsible for including the uComDrv.dll . For COM clients to create instances of Uniface services (call-in), you must have the exported COM Interface DLL for the services on the workstation. You need to register the exported COM Interface DLL in the workstation’s Microsoft Windows Registry. This is handled by the self-registering capability of the DLL, and the standard Microsoft Windows REGSVR32 command. For example, to register the definitions contained in the file SERVS.DLL , use the following command: REGSVR32 SERVS.DLL For COM call-out, the assignment file must contain the appropriate reference to the COM connector path for the desired components. Note: COM-specific assignment file settings are not required if COM is specified as the default implementation in the Signature Editor. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}